Twitter users are unable to log onto the social media website in what the management says its 'fixing'. Those users who had logged onto the site, are able to use it but cannot get trends, notifications,one can't upload media attachments among other features. If you log out and attempt to log in again, a user will receive a screen written "something is technically wrong". "We've been experiencing outages across Twitter and TweetDeck. You might have had trouble Tweeting, getting notifications, or viewing DMs. We're currently working on a fix, and should be back to normal soon," Twitter Support said on Wednesday. Many Twitter users took who were logged in took to other social media platforms to inquire if others were experiencing the same problems. Even though it alerted their users of the outage, it did not say what the problem was. Outage monitoring website Outage.report received more than 4,000 reports of the incident globally, including Japan, Canada and India. A Twitter representative had earlier told Reuters that the company was investigating issues with TweetDeck, which is used by reporters and other content creators for monitoring tweets from multiple Twitter accounts.